# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers for changes that reach the cluster or cloud.
#
# The "Protect Master" ruleset has require_code_owner_review: true, but that only
# bites on paths listed here. These paths are the deploy surface:
#   - deploy/terraform/** : out-of-cluster IaC, applied by FuzeInfra (Cloudflare,
#     nodes, cloud). A bad change here can alter prod infrastructure.
#   - deploy/argocd/**    : Argo Applications (pull-reconciled onto the cluster).
#   - deploy/helm/**      : the prod chart + values-prod (image tags, ingress) that
#     Argo deploys — changes here ship to prod.
#   - .github/workflows/** : CI/CD incl. the infra-dispatch + release pipelines.
# Requiring the infra owner's review on these is the gate that makes "merge = ship"
# safe (the merge approval IS the deploy/apply approval).

# Catch-all: every change requires the owner's review (contribution-ready default,
# from #93). The path-specific entries below are redundant under this but kept to
# document the highest-risk deploy surface explicitly.
* @izzywdev

/deploy/terraform/    @izzywdev
/deploy/argocd/       @izzywdev
/deploy/helm/         @izzywdev
/.github/workflows/   @izzywdev
